---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import WaitlistForm from '../components/WaitlistForm.astro';

const title = 'Denazen — Public when you want. Private when it matters.';
const description = 'A privacy-first social network built on Bluesky. Share publicly when you want to, privately in end-to-end encrypted circles when it matters.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description} pathname="/">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <h1>Public when you want.<br />Private when it matters.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            A social network built on Bluesky, with private circles that only you and the people you choose can read. Not even we can see them.
          </p>
          <WaitlistForm id="waitlist" buttonLabel="Request invite" note="Invite-only alpha. We'll email you when a spot opens." />
        </div>
        <div class="hero-visual">
          <img src="/images/hero-dual-feed.svg" alt="A phone showing a public feed beside a phone showing a private, end-to-end encrypted circle feed." width="520" height="560" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Denazen? -->
  <section class="section-tint">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>Why Denazen?</h2>
        <p>Most social media makes you perform for everyone. Denazen lets you choose.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Public when you want -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-visual">
          <img src="/images/feed-public.svg" alt="Public feed on Denazen — standard Bluesky content, open and discoverable." width="280" height="520" />
        </div>
        <div class="info-text">
          <h2>Public when you want</h2>
          <p>
            Post to the open web like you always have. Denazen is built on the AT Protocol, so your public posts live on Bluesky — followed by whoever follows you, discoverable by anyone.
          </p>
          <p>
            Bring your Bluesky handle. Keep your followers. Nothing about public posting changes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Private when it matters -->
  <section class="section-tint">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-grid reversed">
        <div class="info-text">
          <h2>Private when it matters</h2>
          <p>
            For everything else, Denazen adds a private layer. Posts are end-to-end encrypted on your device before they leave it. Only the people you share with can decrypt them.
          </p>
          <p>
            No one else can see this. Not even us.
          </p>
          <p class="info-actions">
            <a href="/security/" class="btn btn-outline">How the encryption works →</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-visual">
          <img src="/images/feed-private.svg" alt="Private circle feed on Denazen — content visible only to chosen recipients." width="280" height="520" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Circles -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-visual">
          <img src="/images/circles-diagram.svg" alt="Overlapping circles showing one person who belongs to multiple private groups — Family, Close friends, Coworkers." width="480" height="360" />
        </div>
        <div class="info-text">
          <h2>Not everything is for everyone</h2>
          <p>
            Put people into private circles. Each one has its own space. Share with your close friends without broadcasting to coworkers. Share with family without posting for strangers.
          </p>
          <p>
            Circles aren't friend lists. You decide who's in each one, and you can revoke access anytime — cryptographically, not as a promise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feature grid 2x2 -->
  <section class="section-tint">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>Privacy, without the compromise</h2>
        <p>A social network that keeps its promises because it can't break them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <svg class="card-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2"></rect>
            <path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"></path>
          </svg>
          <h3>End-to-end encrypted</h3>
          <p>Private posts are encrypted on your device with AES-256. Decrypted only by the people you've shared with. Denazen's servers see nothing readable.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <svg class="card-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="9" cy="8" r="4"></circle>
            <path d="M3 21v-1a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h0a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v1"></path>
            <circle cx="17" cy="10" r="3"></circle>
            <path d="M15 21v-1a4 4 0 0 1 4-4h0"></path>
          </svg>
          <h3>You control the audience</h3>
          <p>Circles are one-directional and revocable. Remove someone and they lose access — the cryptography enforces it, not a setting.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <svg class="card-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"></circle>
            <path d="M3 12h18"></path>
            <path d="M12 3c2.5 3 3.5 6 3.5 9s-1 6-3.5 9"></path>
            <path d="M12 3c-2.5 3-3.5 6-3.5 9s1 6 3.5 9"></path>
          </svg>
          <h3>Built on AT Protocol</h3>
          <p>Open, portable identity. Use your Bluesky handle — no phone number required. Your public presence stays yours, portable across apps.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <svg class="card-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9 3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1-7.6 4.7 8.38 8.38 0 0 1-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1 4.7-7.6 8.38 8.38 0 0 1 3.8-.9h.5a8.48 8.48 0 0 1 8 8v.5z"></path>
          </svg>
          <h3>Private replies to public posts</h3>
          <p>React to anything on Bluesky inside a circle instead of the timeline. Discuss without broadcasting. Safer commentary without the pile-on.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- No ads / no trackers -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-text">
          <h2>No ads. No trackers. No algorithm deciding what you see.</h2>
          <p>
            Denazen isn't built to keep you scrolling. There are no ads, no behavioral tracking, no feed sorted by what will make you react. Just the people you've chosen to hear from.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're not selling your data. We can't — we can't read it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-visual">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 360 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Three items crossed out: ads, trackers, algorithmic feed.">
            <g font-family="Inter, sans-serif" font-weight="500" font-size="22" fill="#4b5563">
              <g transform="translate(40 60)">
                <text x="0" y="0">Ads</text>
                <line x1="-8" y1="-8" x2="70" y2="-32" stroke="#6B2C91" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </g>
              <g transform="translate(40 140)">
                <text x="0" y="0">Trackers</text>
                <line x1="-8" y1="-8" x2="120" y2="-32" stroke="#6B2C91" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </g>
              <g transform="translate(40 220)">
                <text x="0" y="0">Algorithmic feed</text>
                <line x1="-8" y1="-8" x2="220" y2="-32" stroke="#6B2C91" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </g>
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Secondary waitlist CTA -->
  <section class="section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>Join the alpha</h2>
        <p>Denazen is launching in a small, invite-only alpha. Drop your email and we'll let you know when a spot opens up.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:center;">
        <div>
          <WaitlistForm id="waitlist-footer" buttonLabel="Request invite" note="No spam. One email when your invite is ready." />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
